<h4>About this student app</h4>
<p>
    This app may collect limited account, learning progress, device, and support information so the organization operating it can provide the service, support learners, and understand how the app is being used.
</p>
<p>
    This default notice is provided as boilerplate for Crudspa-based student apps. The school, district, or service provider operating the app may replace it with a product-specific privacy policy.
</p>
<h4>1. Information that may be collected</h4>
<p>
    Depending on how the app is configured, information may include learner names or nicknames, grade or classroom context, parent or teacher contact details, sign-in activity, learning progress, and device or browser details needed to run and support the service.
</p>
<h4>2. How information may be used</h4>
<p>
    Information may be used to create accounts, deliver learning experiences, save progress, provide reports to authorized adults or school staff, maintain the service, troubleshoot issues, and improve the app.
</p>
<h4>3. How information may be shared</h4>
<p>
    Information may be shared with the organization operating the app, with schools or guardians authorized to view learner progress, with service providers working on the operator's behalf, or when disclosure is required by law.
</p>
<h4>4. Security and retention</h4>
<p>
    The operator of this app is responsible for its privacy practices, legal representations, retention schedule, and security review process. Information may be retained only as long as needed to operate the service, meet contractual obligations, resolve support issues, or satisfy legal requirements.
</p>
<h4>5. Questions and updates</h4>
<p>
    For questions about this app's privacy practices, or to request access, correction, or deletion where applicable, contact the school, district, or service provider operating the app. Operators should replace this boilerplate with their own privacy policy before production use.
</p>